page.title: 01General Review
page.content: Three quarters of the area surveyed is sea-level reclaimed marshland used mainly for agriculture. The other quarter is higher ground that follows the division of the Old Saxon Shoreway and rises from five metres above sea-level to sixty metres above sea-level. Hythe Military Canal follows the foot of the escarpment. There is: A Norman Castle Stutfall Castle Lympne Church Lymne Place A Primary School 3 Farms 55 Houses 2 Caravan Parks 2 Public Houses 1 Workshop 1 Tea Shop 1 Dogs' Holiday Home
